FBIS4-36018 "drnes107_j_94019" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 1 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Salih Appreciates Mitterrand's Support for Unity Salih Appreciates Mitterrand's Support for Unity JN0106060194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 0430 GMT 1 Jun 94 JN0106060194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, chairman of the Presidential Council, and President Francois Mitterrand of the friendly French Republic, spoke on the telephone last night. The two leaders discussed relations between the two friendly countries and ways of promoting them to serve common interests. They discussed developments in Yemen after some secessionist, rebellious elements within the Socialist Party ignited a war as a means to achieve their objectives. The brother chairman of the Presidential Council briefed the French president about the reality of what is happening in our country and the brave confrontation of the secessionist rebels to champion unity, democracy, and constitutional legitimacy. The brother chairman of the Presidential Council expressed his extreme appreciation for the position of the French president and France in support of unity, democracy, and party pluralism in our country. The French president reiterated his country's support for Yemeni unity, democratic approach, and development drive.
